They could say they are a 35 year old married man with a good job that just found the game from a friend etc and is very educated. But to people who do not understand, that is a blatant lie.<br>
<br>
To me, Roleplaying is the act of being someone different from yourself, but taking it to a different level beyond the existance that we know. You immerse yourself in a new world and culture, you leave behind everything you know in reality save your typing skills and the dictionary beside your desk! Make notes to your characters description, define who HE is. Leave behind your old life for it is feeble and worthless. Embrace changing your life into this person, give your time and life, your soul into your character. You must make your new vessal this body that walks uppon Norrath, would you make him known as a dastardly bastard or true hearted warrior? <br>
You must first make yourself beleive everyone is 7337 until proven otherwise, if they ask you for a sow, tell them..<br>
&quot;DO I LOOK LIKE A FARMER?&quot; Then proceed to ignore them, or act an NPC and simply tell them to crawl into the sewers for speaking in such incoherant jargon.<br>
<br>
Anyways, those are my ramblings. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueannyarah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eannyarah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/10/01 1:52:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/luclintr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: question</span><hr size=1> Isn't that what I said?  hehe.  You've definitely got a point there.  You did lose me with the 7337 stuff, though...   You also might call roleplaying an &quot;out-of-body experience&quot;.  You forget who you are, where you're from, what your natural tendencies are, and you adopt new ones.  You create yourself anew, you breath air differently, you have a different outlook on life, different motivations, different memories, and a different personality, even.  When you hear an actor say &quot;What's my motivation here?&quot; you understand what he's trying to establish.  When you see an actress take a deep breath and suddenly, BOOM, she is no more and there's a new person standing there, you know what happened.  When you visit a fellow EQer, and a normally nice person that happens to be playing a SK or an evil warrior begins snapping at you and ordering you about, you know what happened.  There prolly isn't really one way to describe/explain RPing.  I liken it to being in love.  You can't understand it, unless you've experienced it.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Neo, being the One is like being in love.  No one can tell you you're in love, you just know it, balls to bones.&quot;  ~The Oracle from &quot;The Matrix&quot; <p>"How can I kill you if you keep stunning me?" ~Eannyarah </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufenye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fenye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen of Discord</span><br>  Posts: 2267<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/11/01 3:23:32 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://people.mn.mediaone.net/timelord81/images/fenye.jpg hieght=285 width=129 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/luclintr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: question</span><hr size=1> Here are some reasons then.<br>
<br>
For fun. Imagining yourself as a powerful knight, a crafy sorcerer, or an evil necromancer can be a thrill for someone who has a vivid imagination. It's almost like dreaming. You get to make your future, you get to slay powerful creatures, you get to do things that you could NEVER do in real life. It's fun to expand your &quot;dreams&quot; to concious thoughts and enjoy them while you are awake.<br>
<br>
For escape. Some people are not happy with thier real lives, so becoming someone they aren't normally is a release to life's stresses. Being someone who is strong, capable of anything, can be very soothing to someone who has pain in RL.<br>
<br>
For revenge. Hate being picked on by bullies? Tired of being dumped by guys/girls? Hate your boss? People put themselves into this fantasy of being a powerful avatar to kill monsters. The act of destroying something that they can symbolize as a pain in thier RL is actually beneficial. It's just a step up from beating the snot out of your punching bag/bedroom wall/kid brother. Much safer, too.<br>
<br>
<br>
Then there is roleplaying in stories. This is entirely different than actually roleplaying yourself. Here you are telling a story, a make-believe or fantasy story about your character or someone else's character. My recent stories are called the Stone Heart. It is of my barbarian warrior, Tilana. In game, I roleplay her as a gladiator escapee. The story deals with her first beginnings, how she came into the gladiator pits, although the story line isn't complete yet. I enjoy writing stories about others almost as much as I enjoy roleplaying myself. At least when I write, other people can enjoy reading them, and that itself makes me happy when someone likes what I read. <br>
<br>
Roleplaying, simply, is another source of fun or relief.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utrizten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trizten</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unhealthy Gnome Obsession</span><br>  Posts: 624<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/17/01 4:09:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question</span><hr size=1> I like to play Everquest.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.showMessage?topicID=426.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.showMessage?topicID=394.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.threadControl?topicID=419.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=419.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=419.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="brellserilisfrm67">Today's News<option value="brellserilisfrm48">Town Crier (Rules & Announcements)<option value="brellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion">The Com